summary: Arunmozhi calls ITC to check on the expiry date of 'Blessings' brand wheat flour. He bought 1KG pack which expires on 20th September. He wants to know if there is any issue with the product quality. The customer care executive takes down the complaint and provides Arunmozhi with a complaint number. The executive also informs Arunmozhi that the product is fit for consumption until 2 months from the expiry date, and that he will inform the concerned team about the issue. They also discuss the batch details and pricing. Arunmozhi is advised to stay on the line while the executive files the complaint and provides a reference number.
speaker_a_summary: Praveen, a customer service representative from ITC, assists a customer with a complaint about a product he purchased. The customer speaks Tamil. The customer bought an auto product, but was unable to finish it. He wants to know if he could get a new product from the market. Praveen takes down the customer's details, including his name (Karuppa), address, and phone number, and promises to get back to him with a complaint number. The customer purchased the product at a price of Rs.123.
speaker_b_summary: The customer is calling about a recent purchase of Blessing Wheat Flour. The expiry date is September 20, and the customer was expecting it to last longer. The customer used 1kg and was disappointed that the packaging was only enough for one use. The customer recently bought 5kg in bulk, and only used 4 of the packs so far. The customer is querying if the product is still safe to use, and is provided with an email for any further queries related to the product.
cohere_points:
- Customer is calling about a bad batch of wheat flour he bought and is requesting a refund.
- ITC Customer Service assures the customer his complaint will be escalated and he will be contacted soon.
- The complaint will be noted and the customer will be informed of next steps. 
- The batch code can be used for reference and the price was also displayed. 
- The customer is then asked to stay on the line while the complaint is being processed.
